cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the study analyzes social media data and examines the behavior of users on Instagram.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the study explores the potential impact of social media on people's relationship with food and health.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the study may involve developing algorithms or software tools to analyze the large dataset of Instagram posts.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the study examines how people interact with food-related content on social media and how it affects their attitudes towards food and health.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the study analyzes visual content (i.e. food photos) on Instagram and may involve image processing techniques.
